        <updateDate>2018-02-14T20:12:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Community Reentry Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to modify requirements with respect to the pre-release placement of inmates in residential reentry centers. Specifically, it adds a requirement for the Bureau of Prisons to place a prisoner in a residential reentry center that is within 50 miles of the prisoner's permanent legal address, subject to bed space availability.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
